HEADWORD: Songster
<hw>Song"ster</hw> <pr>(s⟦ocr⟧ng"st⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[AS. <ets>sangestre</ets> a female singer.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who sings; one skilled in singing; -- not often applied to
human beings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A singing bird.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Songstress</ent>⟦br⟧
